=======
pyHash9
=======

A python module that produces an X13 hash from an input string.


Rationale
---------

This module is useful for chain linearization.



Usage
-----

::
     >>> from pyHash9 import hash9
     >>> hash9("Why did they call it Hash9?")
     '3bddd71f63eb706ca44fd61743b5e23da7497b86db1164c3d2125432bd8d4c31'



Building
--------

::

    % cd pyHash9
    % make



Installation
------------

    % cp pyHash9.so ${PYTHONPATH}


